review:
Went for my mother’s molar extraction as it was already hurting a lot. The tooth extraction was extremely painful with little to no conversation between the doctor and my mother who is 68 years of age. Felt very indifferent kind of approach towards a patient. I would really not visit here again. 

And just to clarify, my mom has had multiple extractions about a year ago with almost no pain before getting 9 artificial teeth fitted, so she is not new to dental procedures.
reply_text: Please list all the drugs your mother was on on the registration form including medical history & therapy. Understand this there’re drug interactions that we have take into account for seamless patient experience. Conditions told post treatment will not be entertained as the consent and health details were signed by you..
